. You also havent specified a balance, so create a balance (uint256 balance;) and then in your payab;e function add the amount received (msg.amount) to the balance stored and then check it in the testcase like so: 
balance = myContract.balance();. Truffle tests dont reset state within the same file, if this is an issue for you, you can use a 'beforeEach' hook and specify a function which creates a new instance of your contract using 'MyContract.new([param1],[param2]...)'
